column5: Any fishing reports from Rainy? Heard that the lake is up due to lots of rain.
Sorry I don't have a report but I'll be heading up to The Fisheries Resort Sat. morning. Where you staying at?
We're also staying at the Fisheries. We'll also arive Saturday morning.
I'll be at the fisheries in late August. Never been there before. When coming from Ft. Francis, you make a LEFT turn off Hwy 11 ??? Let me know how you did on the water. Happy fishing. Ray
go to their Web Site at:http://www.thefisheries.com/
Pathfinder, Look for a group of guys staying in cabin 9. It's on an island. We are running a Lund with 60 Yamaha and a Tracker. Maybe we can share info .

I was there the first week in June and the water was high and still rising. I have been fishing that area for 15 yrs and have never seen the lake so stained and with so much current. The waterfalls woure pouring in dingy reddish brown water and you could not see your lure 2 feet deep. It made the fishing sporadic but hopefully it has cleared up since.
